Expanding Company Wins Prestigious Design Award Dare to Design of Toronto, Canada, was awarded the prestigious Boden Logo Design Award on Thursday for the logo it created for Norman-Brock Regional Hospital (NBRH). The panel of judges agreed that the logo was innovative in its use of color and was likely to be indispensable to creating a recognizable brand for NBRH.
In his acceptance speech, Dare to Design President Marcus Elmore said, “We are honored to receive this award. It is a reflection of the hard work and dedication of each one of our employees." Elmore, a former magazine designer, has headed the company for ten years. He has also supervised the design of over 135 logos. — [1] —. These include logos for companies such as car manufacturer Glenna Motors, kitchen appliance manufacturer Kitchenhelper, and investment bank S. T. Madison.
— [2] —. Dare to Design had announced earlier in the week that it plans to open a second office in Vancouver next year. It has been obtaining more and more contracts from the country's West Coast. — [3] —. "We are growing dramatically, and we hope to serve even more customers next year," Elmore said. "The Boden Logo Design Award only confirms what we already knew. The Dare to Design is able to respond to client needs with originality and professionalism." — [4] —.

SOCIAL MEDIA GROUP FOR RESIDENTS OF LAKEWOOD APARTMENTS Juan Soto [5:15 P.M.]
I created this group for Lakewood Apartment residents. I’m upset by the balcony repairs happening to the building. But, before I raise concerns with the building management, I wanted to make sure I’m not the only one that is bothered by the process.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Gale Banks [5:16 P.M.]
You are not the only one. I’m very unhappy that I wasn’t told which days workers would be going inside my unit in order to access my balcony.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Juan Soto [5:17 P.M.]
Yes! I absolutely agree with you! I don’t like the fact that strangers were in my home without my knowing.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Daniel Cleaves [5:18 P.M.]
That part actually didn’t bother me. However, I do have an issue with the sound of the construction. I understand that this kind of work can’t be quiet, but I don’t think it’s reasonable for any construction to begin at 6 A.M. every day. Many of us are still sleeping!
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Gale Banks [5:18 P.M.]
I’ve noticed that too. It starts that early even on weekends!
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Daniel Cleaves [5:22 P.M.]
My roommates are dissatisfied with the noise as well.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Gale Banks [5:24 P.M.]
I talk about it with people in the elevator all the time. I think most residents are upset.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Daniel Cleaves [5:25 P.M.]
I’ve considered filing a complaint with the building office.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Juan Soto [5:25 P.M.]
Okay, I’m grateful that I’m not alone. I’m going to speak with the building manager today. I’ll bring this up.

Silver Lake Apartments
The newly constructed Silver Lake apartment complex is located in the popular downtown neighborhood of Glenburg. Many units have already been leased, but we are still seeking tenants. The 11-floor building contains 110 apartments. You can choose from the following arrangements:
Studio: $800 per month
Loft: $900 per month
One-bedroom: $1,200 per month
Two-bedroom: $2,100 per month
Three-bedroom: $3,000 per month
Monthly rent includes all utilities, along with the cleaning and general upkeep of the building’s communal areas and private rooftop garden. Apartments come fully furnished, but furnishings may be removed upon request, and a reduction in monthly rent may be negotiable in such cases.
Building amenities include a conference room, a fully-equipped fitness room, a table tennis room, and a top-of-the-line keycard-operated security system at the main entrance. All new tenants will receive a complimentary rug in the color of their choice. To arrange a viewing or request further details, please call 555-8399.-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------To: Gilbert Oliver (goliver@silverlake.com)From: Amy Heaton (amyheaton@kingsley.com)Subject: Apartment 501Date: June 24Attachment: 501tenant.doc
Mr. Fassbender has notified me of his intention to move into apartment 501. I have attached a copy of his lease agreement and personal details. He will go to the Silver Lake main office on July 26 to pay $2,100 up front for the first month of rent for the apartment. His lease officially begins on August 1, and he will arrive with his belongings at around 8 A.M. on that day. Therefore, I have notified the building manager and asked him to have the apartment ready by July 31. Mr. Fassbender chose the dark chocolate rug for the apartment.
I have another client interested in renting your last remaining studio apartment, and a family of four has asked to view the three-bedroom apartment. Once I close those deals, all of the ten apartments you own in the building will be leased. It has been a pleasure representing you and your property interests.

Holistic Medicine Association (HMA Conference Talk Schedule)
			09:00Dr. Wyatt Helms /"Attaining Healthy Weights for Older Patients"
			This talk covers how medical professionals can encourage overweight, aging patients to make lifestyle changes.
			10:00Dr. Sherry Schaal / "Clinical X-rays: Problems and Soutions."
			Despite significant advances in medical imaging technologies, X-rays are still an important diagnostic tool. This talk looks at the advantages and disadvantages of X-rays to modern doctors.
			11:30Dr. Jeff Feldman /"The Spine: An Overview for Non-specialist Physicians."
			Dr. Feldman explores the impact the spine can have on a variety of conditions.
			14:45Dr. Rodney Foster/"Managed Care: Working with Non-medical Staff."
			Handling non-medical staff in a managed care facility for the elderly presents a range of unique challenges for today's general practitioners. Dr. Foster will give practical advice on these matters.
			16:30Dr. Becca Cahill/"Developing Immunizations."
			This talk looks at the difficulties in getting primary care into remote regions all over the world.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------* E-mail *To: All Members (membership@hmaconference.com)From: Hillary Con key (h.conkey@hmaconference.com)Date: February 12Subject: Successful Event
Dear Members,
Once again we have completed a very successful event at the HMA Conference. I was glad to see that the attendance figures showed a 15% increase from last year. I wanted to give you all my thoughts on the conference generally along with some updates.
Firstly, I particularly enjoyed the printed materials handed out to attendees at the X-ray talk. They were useful during the presentation, and I also expect to refer to them in my day-to-day practice.
Secondly, Dr. Foster and Dr. Helms both wanted to express their regret that time constraints made it impossible for them to include the scheduled question-and-answer sessions at the end of their respective lectures. They have, however, agreed to run an online version through the forums on our Web site, www.hmaconference.com, over the next two weeks. So head over there and add your voice to the discussions.
Lastly, in the near future, we will be making a decision on the location of next year’s conference. Details to follow by the end of the month.
Best regards,
Hillary Conkey
President, Holistic Medicine Association

part_7.paragraph:
Saying Goodbye to IronsideBy Emmie Yates
The band Ironside broke the hearts of its fans earlier this year when it announced that the band intends to separate. The trio, which was founded in 2002, has enjoyed a highly successful career that includes three best-selling albums and three world tours. However, guitarist and lead singer Tom Baxley declared that he wanted to leave the band in order to begin a solo career. The other members decided not to continue without him.
However, before the band disassembles officially, it will hold four concerts at the Wilmington Amphitheater over the next two months. The performance dates are January 1, January 15, February 2, and February 24.
Ticket prices vary from $95 to $229 based on distance from the stage. The furthest seats are cheapest. Some critics have remarked that these ticket prices are too high for a farewell performance, but the cost doesn’t appear to bother fans. According to the band’s manager, James Tucker, “Tickets are selling quickly! If you don’t buy soon, you might not get one!” Tickets can be bought online at www.ironsideconcert.com/tickets.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------E-MAIL MESSAGE To: Ray Upton (ray@connection.ca)From: Arlene Payne (payne@mail.com)Date: December 9Subject: Ironside PerformanceAttached: News article
Ray, have you heard the news? Ironside is holding a goodbye tour! I've included an article about it. Ever since we saw them perform the first year they came out, you and I have talked about going to another one of their concerts together. Now we're running out of time to do it! I'd really like to see this concert with you, so we need to plan quickly. Tickets are selling really fast.
I called the concert hall and there's already one show, the one on the 2nd, that's entirely sold out. Likewise, the concert on January 15 only has the cheapest tickets left because all the rest have been sold. Furthermore, I know that you're on vacation over Christmas and New Year's, so that concert date also doesn't work. Hopefully we can work something out, though.
Let me know which date and seating area you prefer as soon as possible. I want us to get tickets before it's too late!
Arlene
